<item>
            <title>[LU-18445] Sleeping before panic in LBUG is wrong</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-18445</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;patch &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/55505&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/55505&lt;/a&gt; introduced a sleeping before panic on lbug, this is actually a bad idea:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;it pollutes the logs with useless data (both lustre and dmesg) and makes sure all sorts of tight races disappear from threads in the crashdump.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This msleep needs to be removed.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
